</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Two communications satellites were lifted into orbit in the fourth of nine 
space flights planned by the European consortium Arianespace. An upgraded 
version of the Ariane 4, Europe's most powerful rocket, carried the double 
payload aloft to complete the European Space Agency's 13th successful mission. 
The three-stage, 192-foot-long rocket, launched from the agency's jungle 
complex in French Guiana, delivered Japan's $100-million Superbird-A 
communications satellite and a West German television-relay station known as 
DFS Kopernikus 1 into orbit. 
