<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN DIEGO COUNTY DIGEST: SAN DIEGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Occupants of two pickup trucks opened fire on each other in a blazing gun 
battle Monday night near the Fashion Valley shopping center that ended with one 
man dead and police searching for suspects. 
</P>
<P>
The unidentified victim, who had been in one of the trucks, was pronounced dead 
at Sharp Memorial Hospital with a chest wound. His name was not released, 
pending notification of his family. 
</P>
<P>
Sgt. Timothy Smith said the shooting occurred about 7 p.m. as two groups of men 
in the trucks began shooting at each other as they drove south on Ulric Street, 
approaching Fashion Valley. 
</P>
<P>
Police found bullet casings from a 9-millimeter pistol, a .22-caliber handgun 
and a .45-caliber weapon in the area, but no suspects were immediately taken 
into custody. 
</P>
<P>
The truck with the wounded man in it stopped just north of Fashion Valley on 
Ulric. The other truck sped away. Paramedics were summoned, and the victim was 
taken by ambulance to the hospital. 
</P>
</TEXT>
