<TEXT>
<P>
"Indiana Jones" star Harrison Ford will be visiting a different kind of temple 
of doom this week as he observes murder trials in Detroit Recorder's Court to 
prepare for a film role as a prosecutor. Ford has been cast as Rozat (Rusty) 
Sabich, a chief assistant prosecutor accused of murder in "Presumed Innocent," 
a movie based on the Scott Turow novel of the same name. After Mirage 
Productions chose Detroit as a location for the film's street scenes, the 
Michigan Prosecutors' Assn. began mailing Ford training films. Chief Assistant 
Prosecutor George Ward says of Ford's visit to Detroit this week: "I feel 
lucky, that of all the chief assistants in the country, my job is being used as 
a model." ALEENE MacMINN 
