<P>
T-Bill Rates Drop: The Treasury sold $6.4 billion of new three-month bills at 
an average discount rate of 8.17%, down from 8.50% last week. Another $6.4 
billion of new six-month bills was sold at an average discount rate of 7.99%, 
down from 8.36% last week. The rates were the lowest since three-month bills 
sold for 8.14% on Dec. 19 and six-month bills averaged 7.87% on Nov. 14. The 
new discount rates understate the actual return to investors -- 8.46% for 
three-month bills, with a $10,000 bill selling for $9,793.50 and 8.44% for a 
six-month bill selling for $9,596.10. The discount rate reflects the price 
discount received when government securities are purchased at less than face 
value. 
