PEOPLE: TIMES MIRROR BROADCASTING TAPS PRESIDENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Carl (Bud) Carey will join Times Mirror as president of Times Mirror 
Broadcasting on July 3. Carey, who also will become a Times Mirror vice 
president, will be responsible for the company's four network-affiliated 
television stations: KDFW-TV in Dallas; KTVI in St. Louis; WVTM-TV in 
Birmingham, Ala., and KTBC-TV in Austin, Tex. Times Mirror Broadcasting's 
offices will be in New York City. 
</P>
<P>
Carey, 44, has been vice president and general manager of WNBC-TV in New York, 
NBC's flagship owned-and-operated station. Before that, he served as station 
manager of KNBC in Los Angeles. Times Mirror is a Los Angeles-based media and 
information company and publishes the Los Angeles Times. 
