</P>
<P>
WOODLAND HILLS GUNMAN KILLS SELF 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and wire service reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
California Highway Patrol officers on patrol early today witnessed a man 
wrestle another man to the ground and shoot him twice in the head during a 
fight in the parking lot of a Woodland Hills high school. 
</P>
<P>
One of the CHP officers wounded the gunman, but he escaped. Shortly after the 
2:50 a.m. shooting, the unidentified man was trailed from Taft High School to a 
nearby office building, where he shot himself to death in a restroom as Los 
Angeles police were preparing to move in. 
</P>
<P>
The man who was wounded in the parking lot was identified as Anthony Rotella, 
21, of Woodland Hills, a community services officer for the Los Angeles County 
Sheriff's Department. Rotella, a civilian employee who worked at the Santa 
Clarita Valley station, was taken to Northridge Hospital Medical Center, where 
he was in critical condition after surgery. 
</P>
<P>
The reasons for the dispute leading to the shooting were not known. 
</P>
</TEXT>
