POPE CONDEMNS ABORTION, DIVORCE AS HE ARRIVES IN LIBERAL DENMARK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
COPENHAGEN 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Pope John Paul II bitterly condemned abortion and divorce as ravages of sin as 
he began a visit today to Denmark, known for its liberal views on sex and the 
family. 
</P>
<P>
It was the first time John Paul raised the subjects on his tour of Scandinavia, 
where attitudes on sex clash sharply with Roman Catholic teachings. 
</P>
<P>
Celebrating a Mass in the park of a monastery, the pontiff said sin in today's 
world takes the form of "widespread indifference to the things of God . . . a 
readiness to disregard human life or manipulate it. . . ." 
</P>
<P>
The Pope was speaking in a country where one abortion is recorded for every 
three births and half the marriages end in divorce. 
</P>
