AUSTRALIAN WINS CYCLE RACE STAGE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MEDA, Italy 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Phil Anderson of Australia won the 17th stage of the Tour of Italy cycling race 
today, edging four pursuers by a few seconds at the finish line. 
</P>
<P>
Frenchman Laurent Fignon, who finished in the pack 15 seconds behind the 
winner, retained the pink jersey of the overall leader with only five stages to 
go. 
</P>
<P>
The 31-year-old Australian led the pack along with Rolf Jaermann of Switzerland 
and Italians Moreno Argentin, Maurizio Fondriest and Gianni Bugno, nine miles 
from Meda. As the Italians and Jaermann prepared for the sprint and controlled 
one another, Anderson sprinted ahead and made it to the finish, scoring his 
first stage victory in the "Giro." 
</P>
<P>
In the overall standings, Fignon held an advantage of 1 minute, 50 seconds over 
Italian runner-up Flavio Giupponi. 
